pageContext.claim: “‘The FBI has no leadership. The Director is protecting the same gang.....that tried to.... ....overthrow the President through an illegal coup.’ (Recommended by previous DOJ) @TomFitton @JudicialWatch”
pageContext.analysis: This tweet is a muddled mess. The two people whom Trump frequently accuses of plotting a coup against him in the FBI, former agent Peter Sztrok and former FBI attorney Lisa Page, no longer work at the bureau. What Trump describes as a coup attempt was actually an investigation into his campaign's dealings with Russia, which was upheld by judges numerous times and for which no evidence of impropriety has emerged.
